cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the topology of online user-object bipartite networks. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it proposes algorithms to improve the recommendation performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) as it deals with the problem of information overload in modern society. The paper also proposes a hybrid method combining time-aware and topology-aware algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) respectively.
